## ğŸš€ Next Steps (30 minutes total)

### 1. Upload to GitHub (5 minutes)
```bash
cd CardioThinkLab-Image-Health-Checker
# Copy all downloaded files to this directory
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit - Image health checker"
git push origin main
```

### 2. Deploy to Streamlit Cloud (5 minutes)
- Go to https://share.streamlit.io
- Connect your GitHub repo
- Click "Deploy"
- Wait 2-3 minutes

### 3. Setup Google Sheets (10 minutes)
- Create Google Cloud service account
- Download JSON credentials
- Share your Google Sheet with service account email
- Add credentials to Streamlit Secrets

### 4. Test! (5 minutes)
- Open your Streamlit app
- Click "Start Image Health Check"
- Watch it crawl and find broken images
- Export to Google Sheets

**Full instructions in DEPLOYMENT.md!**

## ğŸ’¡ How to Use After Deployment

Every time you deploy to production:

1. Open your Streamlit app URL
2. Click "ğŸš€ Start Image Health Check"
3. Wait for scan (usually 2-5 minutes)
4. Review broken images in the dashboard
5. Click "ğŸ“Š Export to Google Sheets"
6. Share sheet with content team
7. Fix broken images
8. Re-run check to verify

